HEADWORD: Land of Steady Habits
<hw>Land of Steady Habits</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>Connecticut; --
a nickname alluding to the moral character of its inhabitants, implied
by the rigid laws (see <er>Blue laws</er>) of the early
period.</def>⟦br⟧
